[2]
Date: 8 Aug 2008
From: Robert Ellis <Robert.Ellis@ColoState.EDU>


Please ask moderator MHJ to check his math regarding the bison
density, he stated "Initially we were told the ranch had 3000 bison,
now it is 4000; possibly the latter number includes calves. With a
ranch size of 13 343 acres [5400 ha] that is 3.3 to 4.4 animals per
acre," -- it should be acres per animal. This is still very dense for
western range standards, but for irrigated and rotated pastures, it
would be pretty well within range of carrying capacity.

--
Communicated by:
Robert Ellis
<Robert.Ellis@ColoState.EDU>

